import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['temperature'], data['pressure'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between temperature and pressure?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Pressure')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['wind'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['wind'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['wind'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['wind'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['wind'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wind speed?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['time_of_day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time_of_day'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='coerce').dt.time
    data = data.groupby('time_of_day')['temperature'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['time_of_day'], data['temperature'])
    plt.title('What is the average temperature by time of day?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Time of Day')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['hour'] = pd.to_datetime(data['hour'], format='%H:%M:%S').dt.hour
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['hour'] == i]['pressure'] for i in range(24)], showfliers=False)
    ax.set_xticklabels([f'{i}:00' for i in range(24)])
    ax.set_xlabel('Hour')
    ax.set_ylabel('Pressure')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of pressure by hour?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
